(* Beginning of Notebook Content *)
Notebook[{
Cell[TextData[{
 "When I taught Quantum I in the Spring of 2007 I took Griffiths' book as my \
nominal text, but illustrated/amplified/animated that material in the present \
collection of ",
 StyleBox["Mathematica",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " notebooks. Most lectures took place with this material projected on a \
screen visible to the class.\n\nThe notebooks were written in ",
 StyleBox["Mathematica",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " 5.2. I have today  used automatic resources to render them compatible with \
",
 StyleBox["Mathematica",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " 6. This means that all animations are still presented in the old style, as \
activated lists of figures. No use is made here of ",
 StyleBox["Animate", "Input"],
 " or ",
 StyleBox["Manipulate", "Input"],
 ". I have not worked through each notebook to make certain that everything \
does in fact work as intended.\n\n\nNicholas Wheeler\nReed College Physics \
Department\n14 December 2007"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.4066568305629587`*^9, 3.406657301116089*^9}}]
},
WindowSize->{640, 750},
WindowMargins->{{529, Automatic}, {146, Automatic}},
FrontEndVersion->"6.0 for Mac OS X PowerPC (32-bit) (June 19, 2007)",
StyleDefinitions->"Default.nb"
]
